qa_pairs.q: What is human life expectancy in the United States?
qa_pairs.a: Human life expectancy in the United States is 78 years.

qa_pairs.q: Who was president of the United States in 1955?
qa_pairs.a: Dwight D. Eisenhower was president of the United States in 1955.

qa_pairs.q: What party did he belong to?
qa_pairs.a: He belonged to the Republican Party.

qa_pairs.q: Who was president of the United States before George W. Bush?
qa_pairs.a: Bill Clinton was president of the United States before George W. Bush.

qa_pairs.q: Who won the World Series in 1995?
qa_pairs.a: The Atlanta Braves won the World Series in 1995.
